st accommodations facility provided at the helm of Dhikala Forest. It is a popular opinion that a wildlife trip in Uttarakhand is incomplete if you have not made a visit to this beautiful Lodge. The beauty around the lodge and the amazing wildlife experience of the forest is worth going on vacation here. Far away from the noise and pollution of city life, this is the trip which will facilitate in developing a deep connection with Nature. With thousands of variety of birds and animals, this is a dream spot of the photographers and they wish to assimilate each and every possible moment. The Royal Bengal Tiger, the elephant, Leopard, and cheetah are no less than any treat to watch. Only a few national parks give you the privilege to stay at the mid of them overnight and Corbett is one of them. Although it seems a bit fearful at the end, it will be the most exciting one ever.</p>\r\n                        <p>The Indians and the SAARC visitors have to book this place for about 46 days in advanced and the tourists from other foreign countries have to book this accommodation for about 91 days in advance. There are six different wings in the Dhikala Forest Lodge which can be categorized as follows:</p>\r\n                        <p>You will also find the accommodation facilities being available at Bijrani, Gairal, Jhirna, and Kanda Forest rest houses. The government is continuously making the efforts in order to increase the accommodation by adding annexes and dormitories. The Solar electric fences around the accommodation are strong enough to ensure your safe night at this place.</p>\r\n                    </div>', '<section class=\"package_content\">\r\n      <div class=\"container mt-3\">\r\n        <div class=\"block\">\r\n          <div class=\"content\">\r\n            <p>Explore the beauty and wilderness of Jim Corbett National Park, often referred to as the <b>\'Land of Roar, Trumpet, and Song.\'</b> Nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas in Uttarakhand, India, 