(22, 'jungle', 'About Jim Corbett Page', 'About Jim Corbett Page', 'jungle_leafbg2.png', 'About Jim Corbett Page', 'About Jim Corbett Page', 'testing', 'testing', '<div id=\"family\" class=\"gallery-page-box\">\r\n        <div class=\"container\">\r\n            <div class=\"row \">\r\n                <div class=\"col-lg-12\">\r\n                    <div class=\"title-box\" style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\">\r\n                        <h2>What is<span> Jim Corbett </span>National Park</h2>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        Jim Corbett National Park is a wild place in Uttarakhand and people can enjoy thrilling safari rides\r\n                        in this wild area. This park is famous among wildlife lovers because it offers sightings of wild\r\n                        animals in their natural habitat. Many people come here to see animals in their natural\r\n                        surroundings. This park is a special spot and people who are coming to the area should definitely\r\n                        enjoy a safari ride at this scenic place.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        This park was established back in 1936 and it has the aim of protecting the endangered Bengal tiger.\r\n                        The famous tiger project was also launched from this wild park on April 1st, 1973. This park is\r\n                        among India’s most attractive national parks with lush greenery and various wildlife sightings. It\r\n                        covers a huge area of 520 sq km and around 650 species of birds call this park a home. Other than\r\n                        birds and tigers, one can find here many animals like leopards, elephants, spotted deer, sambar,\r\n                        nilgai, hog deer, barking deer, sloth bear, wild boar, ghural, langur and rhesus monkey, etc.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"row \">\r\n                <div class=\"col-lg-12\">\r\n                    <div class=\"title-box\" style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\">\r\n                        <h2>What<span> This Park </span>Offers?</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            This park is in Uttarakhand’s Nainital district and people who come here can enjoy many things:\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <div class=\"text-dsg\">\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                One can enjoy a jeep, canter, or elephant safari. Among different safaris, adults, and\r\n                                youngsters like the jeep safari, and mostly kids like the elephant safari. Canters are best\r\n                                for big groups of 10 - 15 people because they can accommodate around 16 people. You can\r\n                                choose any kind of safari that you like. The safari takes place inside the particular zones\r\n                                of the park and those zones have assigned routes for safaris. It has 8 zones named as\r\n                                Jhirna, Dhela, Bijrani, Dhikala, Durgadevi, Sonanadi, Pakhro, and Garjia.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"text-dsg1 mt-4\">\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Apart from safari rides, this park has a museum and it has information about the\r\n                                conservation\r\n                                or the history of Corbett Tiger Reserve. One can visit there and the museum has belongings\r\n                                of Jim Corbett like his final hunt, letters, photographs, manuscripts, etc. People can also\r\n                                purchase different handcrafted items from that place.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                To gain more information about this park, people can visit the Corbett Interpretation Center\r\n                                and Butterfly Park.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"mt-4\">\r\n                    <div class=\"row\">\r\n                        <div class=\"title-box\" style=\"margin-bottom: 5px;\">\r\n                            <h2>Zones <span>Of Jim</span> Corbett </h2>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                This wild park has 8 tourism zones so that people can enjoy unique animal sighting\r\n                                experiences. Every zone has a different route and each zone offers different experiences.\r\n                                Let’s know about them in detail\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Jhirna Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This zone is open all the year and people can enjoy a ride here at any time. Animals\r\n                                        like sloth bears and majestic wild elephants are found here in most numbers and one\r\n                                        can spot them easily. Other animals that can be spotted on Luck include wild bears,\r\n                                        jackals, tuskers, sambar, species of deer, and birds like hornbill, woodpecker, owl,\r\n                                        eagle, etc.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Dhela Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        Just like Jhirna, this one remains open all around the year. It was newly opened in\r\n                                        December 2014 and trees like Sal, Haldu, Bahera, Rohini, and Kusum can be seen here.\r\n                                        One can enjoy the natural beauty of this zone with magical birds chirping sounds.\r\n                                        Animals like elephants, sloth bears, and king cobras can be spotted here apart from\r\n                                        beautiful birds.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Bijrani Zone</b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This zone is not open during monsoons, it only remains open from 15 Oct to 30 June\r\n                                        This zone is widely famous among people and it has good scenic views. It has a large\r\n                                        grassland area which provides the perfect area for tigers so yes, they can be\r\n                                        spotted here. Other animals like wild elephants, sloth bears, and beautiful birds\r\n                                        can also be spotted here near water streams.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Dhikala Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This one is among the most famous zones and it remains open from Nov to June every\r\n                                        year. It has a huge grassland area which provides the best food option for\r\n                                        herbivores. Barking deer, Spotted deer, wild boars, etc. can be easily spotted\r\n                                        grazing here. Tigers and leopards pay a visit here to hunt those herbivores. This\r\n                                        zone also has attraction spots.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Durgadevi Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This zone remains open only from 15 Nov to 15 June and remains closed during other\r\n                                        times. This one is a hilly area and it has a particular sighting area known as\r\n                                        Domunda Bridge where elephants and otters can be spotted. Here you can spot a lot of\r\n                                        different species of birds in good numbers. Masheer fish can also be seen here.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Sitabani Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        Here sightings of herbivores are possible like elephants, deer, sambars, Nilgai, and\r\n                                        many more. It’s the safest zone to come with kids and sightings of animals like\r\n                                        tigers and leopards are not possible here. It has various river streams where\r\n                                        beautiful birds can be spotted. This one is the most scenic zone of the park that\r\n                                        will be best for nature lovers.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Garjia Zone</b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This one is always open and is widely famous among locals as Ringora Zone. It has\r\n                                        dense forests and natural beauty that attracts tourists to see flowering plants. It\r\n                                        is in the most picturesque part and it’s a calm place. Many sots (small water\r\n                                        streams) are there in the zone where many animals can be spotted drinking water.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12\">\r\n                            <div class=\"zone-inner\">\r\n                                <div class=\"zone-img\">\r\n                                    <img class=\"img-fluid locationimage\" src=\"/front/assets/img/desti3.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <h2> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-earth-asia\"></i> <b>Phato Zone </b></h2>\r\n                                <div class=\"wrapper1\">\r\n                                    <div class=\"description readmore\">\r\n                                        This zone is open at all times and it offers sightings of beautiful flowering trees.\r\n                                        You can enjoy a magical experience of natural beauty by coming here. Rare birds can\r\n                                        be spotted here and you can click some nice pictures at this place. It has a\r\n                                        treehouse and elephants are the most seen animal in this zone.\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>', '<div id=\"wedding\" class=\"wedding-box\">\r\n        <div class=\"container\">\r\n            <div class=\"row mb-3\">\r\n                <div class=\"col-lg-12\">\r\n                    <div class=\"title-box\">\r\n                        <h2>How To Reach <span>Jim Corbate</span> National Park</h2>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            Jim Corbett is a famous spot and it is located in the Uttarakhand’s Nainital and Pauri\r\n                            Garhwal districts. The nearest city to this scenic and wild park is Ramnagar and it can be\r\n                            easily reached. One can easily get to this place by bus, train, road, or flight.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"\">\r\n                        <table class=\"second-table\" style=\"text-align: center!important;\">\r\n                            <tbody>\r\n                                <tr class=\"heading-table\" style=\"background:var(--secondary)!important; color: var(--white); text-align: center!important;\">\r\n                                    <th class=\"p-2\" style=\"width: 150px; border:1px solid var(--primary);\">\r\n                                        Source\r\n                                    </th>\r\n                                    <th class=\"p-2 \" style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary);\">\r\n                                        Description\r\n                                    </th>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                                <tr style=\"background: #fff; color:rgb(55, 54, 54); font-weight:500;\">\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\" class=\"fw-semibold\"> By Road</td>\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\">\r\n                                        This city has a good road network with various cities and one can come here\r\n                                        without worrying about transportation options. This spot is 260 km from Delhi so\r\n                                        one can think, how much easy it would be to come here by road. The road towards\r\n                                        this park is in good condition so one can come here easily by bus or by own\r\n                                        vehicle.\r\n                                    </td>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                                <tr style=\"background: rgb(242, 241, 241); color:rgb(55, 54, 54);  font-weight:500\">\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\" class=\"fw-semibold\"> By Train </td>\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\">\r\n                                        Now, the nearest railhead is at Ramnagar\r\n                                        which has a good connection with cities like Delhi, Lucknow, Mumbai, Moradabad,\r\n                                        Varanasi, Haridwar, and many more. From the airport and railhead, one can find\r\n                                        many taxis, buses, or local transport to reach the park.\r\n                                    </td>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                                <tr style=\"background: #fff; color:rgb(55, 54, 54);  font-weight:500\">\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\" class=\"fw-semibold\"> By Bus</td>\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\">\r\n                                        Again Ramnagar is the popular destination as buses from places like Delhi,\r\n                                        Haridwar, Dehradun and other places. One can take a bus to Ramnagar and from\r\n                                        there it’s quite easy to reach the wild area of Corbett National Park..\r\n                                    </td>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                                <tr style=\"background: rgb(242, 241, 241); color:rgb(55, 54, 54);  font-weight:500\">\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\" class=\"fw-semibold\">By Air </td>\r\n                                    <td style=\"border:1px solid var(--primary)\">\r\n                                        This area does not have an airport,\r\n                                        however, one can come to the Phoolbagh airport in Pantnagar which is around 70\r\n                                        km. If someone is coming from other countries then the nearest international\r\n                                        airport is in Delhi which is just 250 km.\r\n                                    </td>\r\n                                </tr>\r\n                            </tbody>\r\n                        </table>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"row m-1\">\r\n            <div class=\"col-lg-12\">\r\n                <iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" id=\"gmap_canvas\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?width=520&amp;height=400&amp;hl=en&amp;q=Jim%20Corbett%20National%20Park%20uttrakhand+()&amp;t=&amp;z=12&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;iwloc=B&amp;output=embed\"></iframe>\r\n                <a href=\"https://www.acadoo-medizin.com/\">Doktorarbeit Medizin Ghostwriter</a>\r\n                <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://embedmaps.com/google-maps-authorization/script.js?id=175fe72ec07e6785e22afa37457c73f90239a0fe\">\r\n                </script>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '2024-03-04 11:24:11', '2024-08-13 07:28:24');
INSERT INTO `page_management` (`id`, `type`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `image`, `banner_image_alt`, `title`, `heading`, `subheading`, `section_1`, `section_2`, `section_3`, `section_4`, `section_5`, `section_6`, `section_7`, `section_8`, `section_9`, `section_10`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(23, 'devalia', 'Chambal Safari Page', 'Chambal Safari Page', 'devalia_leafbg2.png', 'Chambal Safari Page', 'Chambal Safari Page', 'testing', 'testing', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n                <div class=\"row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"col chmbal-safari\"></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container pt-4\">\r\n                <div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-center\">\r\n                    <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n                        <img class=\"img-crush\" src=\"https://ranthamboretigerreserve.in/image/underwater.jpeg\">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"col-lg-6 cmbal-boxs p-3\">\r\n                        <h4 class=\"main_heading\">\r\n                            National Chambal Sanctuary Palighat: The Amusing Dwelling of Underwater\r\n                            Beasts\r\n                        </h4>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            <b>Ranthambhore - </b> name of the renowned National Park of India resonates as the habitat of\r\n                            Royal Bengal tigers and is located in Southeastern Rajasthan\'s Sawai Madhopur district. But, the\r\n                            grandeur of the region\r\n                            doesn\'t conclude with only the regality of the majestic beasts, as several other places in Sawai\r\n                            Madhopur are standing as evidence of natural vivification.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            A visit to the National Chambal Gharial Wildlife Sanctuary covering a tri-state protected area\r\n                            of 2,100sq mi, 45 km far from the Ranthambhore reserve, would be enough for discerning it. On\r\n                            1979\'s December 7, the\r\n                            forest was listed as a National Sanctuary in an attempt of saving the endangered crocodile\r\n                            species.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            The crocodile safari in National Chambal Sanctuary sparkles with an exquisite event to witness\r\n                            the wealth of profusion of birds, and aquatic species like crocodiles, turtles, Ganges dolphins,\r\n                            and others. Therefore,\r\n                            the anecdote of you visiting the area with your friends and family, gazing across the banks of\r\n                            the Chambal River, being attentive to the sudden grunts and chirps, would be something to\r\n                            treasure.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            Therefore, in the following sections, we have discussed everything you need to know if you are\r\n                            intending to experience the Chambal Safari.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-center mt-5\">\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-6 order-lg-2 p-5 crush-mrg\">\r\n                            <img class=\"img-crush\" src=\"https://ranthamboretigerreserve.in/image/crocodile.jpeg\">\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"col-lg-6 cmbal-boxs p-3 order-lg-1\">\r\n                            <h4 class=\"main_heading\">\r\n                                Why is Chambal Safari the Best Option for Tourists Looking to Explore\r\n                                Nearby Places of Ranthambhore?\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                With the promise of permitting you to spend your holidays with nature, the crocodile safari\r\n                                at Palighat will bring opportunities to beholding several aquatic species like red-crowned\r\n                                roof turtles, Ganges river\r\n                                dolphins, Indian roofed turtles, and smooth-coated otters. Besides, the famous gharials and\r\n                                mugger crocodiles of the Chambal River will be among the zenith attractions.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                The boat ride through the Chambal River also denotes fine chances of beholding several kinds\r\n                                of birds as over 320 species of resident and migratory birds can be found within the\r\n                                sanctuary. Some of the mentionable\r\n                                ones from them are sarus crane, Indian skimmer, Indian courser, and Pallas\'s fish eagle.\r\n                                They reside on the pygmean and thorny vegetation spread across the banks of the river.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                You will relish every breath of your journey of a serene boat ride through the quietly\r\n                                surging waters of the Chambal River, alongside the scenic landscapes, while the Chambal\r\n                                Safari boat ride will be conducted\r\n                                through three Indian states – Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, and Rajasthan.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container-fluid\" style=\"color: rgb(20, 19, 19); background: #f7e9d5;\">\r\n                <div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-center mt-5\">\r\n                    <h4 class=\"text-center\" style=\"color: #7e3822;\">Chambal Gharial Safari Booking &nbsp;<img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/15611/15611890.png\" height=\"80px\" width=\"80px\">\r\n                    </h4>\r\n                    <div class=\"col-lg-11\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            The first point to know before planning a safari trip to National Chambal Gharial Wildlife\r\n                            Sanctuary is the booking can\'t be done offline. Meaning, if you are planning a trip to\r\n                            Ranthambhore and want to keep a day\r\n                            for Chambal Safari, you need to pre-book it through www.ranthamboretigerreserve.in At the time\r\n                            of booking, you should share information like names, gender, and age of the visitors going to\r\n                            attend the safari. Identity\r\n                            proof of the partaking visitors will also be mandatory for the online booking process.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p class=\"fst-italic fw-semibold\" style=\"color: #ec8422;\">\r\n                            You will find 4 booking options with different inclusions and benefits, costing 500rs for each\r\n                            individual. You can book the option you like from them. the options and facilities associated\r\n                            with them are following.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <div class=\"d-flex pb-3\">\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                <img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/16691/16691958.png\" height=\"50px\">\r\n                            </span>\r\n\r\n                            <p class=\"px-3 pt-2\">The first option is only for the Chambal Safari where every individual\r\n                                participating in it would be given life jackets.</p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"d-flex pb-3\">\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                <img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/16691/16691993.png\" height=\"50px\">\r\n                            </span>\r\n                            <p class=\"px-3 pt-2\">\r\n                                The second booking option also includes the safari and life jackets. But, as an added\r\n                                facility, you will avail of a pick and drop service to reach the safari destination from\r\n                                your hotel and go back again after\r\n                                the completion of your tour.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"d-flex pb-3\">\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                <img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/16692/16692038.png\" height=\"50px\">\r\n                            </span>\r\n                            <p class=\"px-3 pt-2\">\r\n                                This option excludes the pick and drop facility. But, during your trip, scrumptious lunch\r\n                                will be served for you.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        <div class=\"d-flex pb-3\">\r\n                            <span>\r\n                                <img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/16692/16692082.png\" height=\"50px\">\r\n                            </span>\r\n                            <p class=\"px-3 pt-2\">\r\n                                Option 4 is what you should choose if you are reluctant to leave any of the aforementioned\r\n                                benefits. Meaning, on choosing it, apart from receiving life jackets during your boat ride,\r\n                                you will obtain the pick and\r\n                                drop facility, and delicious meals in lunch too.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-center mt-5\">\r\n                    <h5 class=\"main_heading text-center\">&nbsp;\r\n                        How to Book Pre-Book Vehicles Online For Chambal Safari\r\n                        ?&nbsp;\r\n                    </h5>\r\n                    <div class=\"col pt-3\">\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            You can also pre-book vehicles for your Chambal safari days through\r\n                            <mark>\r\n                                <a href=\"www.ranthamboretigerreserve.in\" class=\"text-dark\">\r\n                                    www.ranthamboretigerreserve.in\r\n                                </a>\r\n                            </mark> the site, you will be able\r\n                            to choose any\r\n                            vehicle from Deluxe, Semi-Deluxe, Luxury, coach, budget, and cheap cars according to your needs.\r\n                            And, all the cars available there encompass the latest safety features and amenities to embrace\r\n                            your journey with\r\n                            convenience, comfort, and safety. Despite offering the convenience of cab booking at a highly\r\n                            competitive rate, the chauffeurs who come along the cars are well-behaved, informed about the\r\n                            routes, and can converse in\r\n                            English and other languages.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                        <p>\r\n                            To book a car, you need to go to the car rental page of\r\n                            <mark>\r\n                                <a href=\"www.ranthamboretigerreserve.in\" class=\"text-dark\">\r\n                                    www.ranthamboretigerreserve.in\r\n                                </a>\r\n                            </mark>\r\n                            There you will find an online form asking for information like your name, phone number, date of\r\n                            your arrival, type of car you require, number of adults and children, their age, your budget,\r\n                            duration of the trip, and\r\n                            more. All you need to do is enter the information without any error and submit them. And, the\r\n                            car will attain you in time right after you arrive at Ranthambhore.\r\n                        </p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-center mt-5\">\r\n                    <h5 class=\"text-start\">\r\n                        <img src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/1168/1168847.png\" width=\"50px\" height=\"50px\">\r\n                        <span class=\"fw-semibold fs-5\" style=\"color: #c25107;\"> &nbsp;\r\n                            Timings of Chambal Safari\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </h5>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        You will be happy to know that for attaining the Chambal safari, you don\'t need to be present at the\r\n                        spot at a strict and lone time frame as the safari gets conducted multiple times in a day. To be\r\n                        more precise, the\r\n                        hour-long safari trips are organized 10 times every day, and you can book any one of them according\r\n                        to the time you find comfortable for you.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p class=\"para-notes p-3\">\r\n                        The first safari starts at 8:00 am and the last one takes place at 5:00 pm.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<section>\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"row\">\r\n                    <div class=\"col-sm-12 col-xs-12\">\r\n                        <div class=\"\">\r\n                            <div class=\"title fs-5 mb-2\" style=\"color: #c25107;\">\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Some Do\'s and Don\'t You Should Keep\r\n                                    in Mind during the Safari\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    You will be happy to know that for attaining the Chambal safari, you don\'t need to be\r\n                                    present at the spot at a strict and lone time frame as the safari gets conducted\r\n                                    multiple times in a day. To be more\r\n                                    precise, the hour-long safari trips are organized 10 times every day, and you can book\r\n                                    any one of them according to the time you find comfortable for you.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    The joy of witnessing a lengthy green gharial resting under the sun at the muddy banks\r\n                                    of the river Chambal is indeed incomparable. However, it shouldn\'t make you negligent\r\n                                    towards the safeties required to be\r\n                                    followed strictly during the boat ride. The deeds you should restrain yourself from\r\n                                    while on the Chambal waters are mentioned below.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n                                <img alt=\"right-arrow\" src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/10570/10570072.png\" width=\"32px\" height=\"32px\">\r\n                                <p class=\"p-1\">&nbsp;\r\n                                    Always sit on the boat after wearing the safety jacket and don\'t try\r\n                                    to pull it out until you are out of the water.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n                                <img alt=\"right-arrow\" src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/10570/10570072.png\" width=\"32px\" height=\"32px\">\r\n                                <p class=\"p-1\">&nbsp;Keep yourself from intentions of swimming.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n                                <img alt=\"right-arrow\" src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/10570/10570072.png\" width=\"32px\" height=\"32px\">\r\n                                <p class=\"p-1\">&nbsp;Don\'t try to drink water from the river.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n\r\n                            <div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n                                <img alt=\"right-arrow\" src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/10570/10570072.png\" width=\"32px\" height=\"32px\">\r\n                                <p>&nbsp; Please don\'t throw any waste on the river as it can harm the species living\r\n                                    within.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n\r\n                            <div class=\"d-flex\">\r\n                                <img alt=\"right-arrow\" src=\"https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/128/10570/10570072.png\" width=\"32px\" height=\"32px\">\r\n                                <p>&nbsp; It\'s better not to dip your hands or feet on the water.</p>\r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '2024-03-04 11:24:10', '2024-07-19 07:03:15'),
(24, 'kankai', 'Gir Kankai Safari Page', 'Gir Kankai Safari Page', 'kankai_leafbg2.png', 'Gir Kankai Safari Page', 'Gir Kankai Safari Page', 'testing', 'testing', '<div class=\"col-lg-6 d-flex align-items-center\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n            <div class=\"content\">\r\n              <!-- <h3>Tarrif</h3> -->\r\n              <table class=\"table-bordered\">\r\n                <thead class=\"\">\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <th colspan=\"2\" class=\"py-3 px-6 text-center\">\r\n                      Kankai Temple Ride Tarrif\r\n                    </th>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                  <tr class=\"bg-white\">\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Temple Visit Area</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Kankai Temple Visit (Maximum 6 Adults and 1 Child are\r\n                      allowed in 1 CAR)\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Price (Indian)</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Prices May Vary, Between 6000 to 8500 ( Inclusive of\r\n                      Cab, Entrance fee, Services &amp; Taxes ) Depends on\r\n                      Weekends, Number of Persons, Festivals, Long Weekends\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr class=\"bg-white\">\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Price (Foreigner)</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Prices May Vary, Between 6000 to 8500 ( Inclusive of\r\n                      Cab, Entrance fee, Services &amp; Taxes ) Depends on\r\n                      Weekends, Number of Persons, Festivals, Long Weekends\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Note</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      The Payment does not guarantee BOOKING Confirmed,\r\n                      BOOKING would be available only as per seat\r\n                      availability, After payment, visitors will, have to call\r\n                      us to confirm there booking.If the booking is not\r\n                      available, your booking will be rescheduled for another\r\n                      date and time with your consent, or will be refunded.\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n              </table>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>', '<!-- ======= Constructions Section ======= -->\r\n    <section id=\"constructions\" class=\"constructions\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>KANKAI TEMPLE INFORMATION</h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            There is a temple which is located 25 km inside Gir National Park.\r\n            People call this temple Kankai Mata Temple or Kankai Mata Shrine.\r\n            This temple is devoted to a holy goddess Kankai and locals believe\r\n            that she is the savior of the shepherds roaming in Gir National\r\n            Park. Pilgrims visit here to seek blessings whereas many wildlife\r\n            enthusiasts visit here because of the safari ride. Kankai Safari\r\n            will start from the gate of Gir National Park which will take you\r\n            25 km inside Gir National Park between forest areas. During your\r\n            ride, you can spot various kinds of animals along with Asiatic\r\n            Lions if you are lucky. The green forest surroundings of this\r\n            temple add a unique charm to its spirituality. If you’re in the\r\n            area of Gir National Park then you should book Kankai Safari Ride\r\n            for a thrilling experience.\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <!-- End Constructions Section -->', '<!-- ======= Services Section ======= -->\r\n    <div id=\"services\" class=\"services\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>KANKAI SAFARI BOOKING DETAILS</h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            The safari runs from 6:30 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. and 1:00 p.m. to 5:00\r\n            p.m. If you wanna go on Kankai Safari then you just have to fill\r\n            out an easy form with details like your name, contact info, email,\r\n            and trip date. You have to fill out how many adults and kids are\r\n            coming along because the forest department only allows up to six\r\n            adults and one child per jeep. Once you fill in all these details,\r\n            just make the payment, and your booking is confirmed.\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <!-- End Services Section -->', '<!-- ======= Services Section ======= -->\r\n    <section id=\"services\" class=\"services\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>FESTIVAL AND CELEBRATION AT KANKAI</h2>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 20px\">\r\n              If you\'re planning to visit Kankai Mata Temple then you should\r\n              visit during festivals as it\'s a whole different vibe. One of\r\n              the prominent festivals is Navaratri, a nine-night festival all\r\n              about honoring Goddess Durga. This one is most biggest because\r\n              Kankai Mata is seen as a form of Goddess Durga herself. During\r\n              this festival, locals are engaged in beating drums and singing\r\n              devotional songs. Plus, you\'ll see everyone wearing traditional\r\n              clothes in all sorts of vibrant colors, making the whole place\r\n              feel like a party of joyful devotion. It\'s an experience you\r\n              don\'t wanna miss.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <br>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <!-- End Services Section -->', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '2024-03-04 11:24:09', '2024-03-16 02:37:05'),
(25, 'girnar', 'Gir Girnar Safari Page', 'Gir Girnar Safari Page', 'girnar_leafbg2.png', 'Gir Girnar Safari Page', 'Gir Girnar Safari Page', 'testing', 'testing', '<div class=\"col-lg-6 d-flex align-items-center\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n            <div class=\"content\">\r\n              <!-- <h3>Tarrif</h3> -->\r\n              <table class=\"table-bordered\">\r\n                <thead class=\"\">\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <th colspan=\"2\" class=\"py-3 px-6 text-center\">\r\n                      Girnar Nature Safari Booking -Tariff\r\n                    </th>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                </thead>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                  <tr class=\"bg-white\">\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Safari Zones</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Girnar Nature Safari (Maximum 6 Adults and 1 Child are\r\n                      allowed in 1 Jeep)\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Price (Indian)</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Prices may vary, Between 4300 to 6500 (Inclusive of\r\n                      Permit, Gypsy &amp; Guide Charges, Services &amp; Taxes)\r\n                      Depends on Weekends, Number of Persons, Festivals, Long\r\n                      Weekends\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr class=\"bg-white\">\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Price (Foreigner)</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      Prices may vary, Between 15500 to 17500 (Inclusive of\r\n                      Permit, Gypsy &amp; Guide Charges, Services &amp; Taxes)\r\n                      Depends on Weekends, Number of Persons, Festivals, Long\r\n                      Weekends\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">Note</td>\r\n                    <td class=\"py-3 px-6\">\r\n                      The Payment does not guarantee booking confirmation.\r\n                      Booking would be available only as per seat\r\n                      availability. After payment, visitors will have to call\r\n                      us to confirm their booking. If the booking is not\r\n                      available, your booking will be rescheduled for another\r\n                      date and time with your consent or will be refunded.\r\n                    </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n              </table>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>', '<section id=\"constructions\" class=\"constructions\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>Girnar Nature Safari\r\n          </h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            Girnar Nature Safari takes place in Girnar Sanctuary. All other parks may have zones for safari or have different routes but there is nothing like that in Girnar Safari, only 1 route has been made for this safari. The safari will start from Indreshwar Naka and will take you 13 km inside the jungle till Paturan beats and then return on the same route. Book your ride quickly because only 8 are allowed each day. The government has only allowed 4 rides in the morning and 4 in the evening. 6 people with 1 kid can go on a safari, the kid should be between 3 to 12 years old. You can spot different kinds of animals during your safari like lions, leopards, deer, crocs, and a bunch more. You can also spot various kinds of birds here. Going on this safari ride is a great way to learn about the flora and fauna because you can ask the guides about the same. \r\n    \r\n          </p>\r\n          <p>Take note that this safari ride remains closed during Girnar Parikrama and Shivratri fair because many pilgrims visit Junagadh during these two festivals.\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>', '<section id=\"constructions\" class=\"constructions\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>Let’s Know About Girnar Sanctuary\r\n          </h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            Girnar Sanctuary is a famous place in Gujarat, India. This place is home to many different kinds of plants and animals. It officially became a wildlife spot in 2008 and the safaris are started here in 2021. These safaris are started to ease the crowd at Gir National Park. Apart from being a pilgrimage spot, this area is home to loads of animals like lions, leopards, deer, crocs, jackals, hyenas, and tons of birds. You can see a lot of wild animals in their natural habitat if you book Girnar Safari. \r\n\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>', '<!-- ======= Constructions Section ======= -->\r\n<section id=\"constructions\" class=\"constructions\">\r\n<div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n  <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n    <h2>GIRNAR HILLS</h2>\r\n    <p>\r\n      Girnar Hills is an awesome place in Junagadh district of Gujarat. They are mountains which are a mix of nature and religion. You can find many historical monuments in this area. Girnar Hills shows off India\'s awesome mix of culture and nature. These hills attract large numbers of Hindus and Jains from all over the world. It’s a famous pilgrimage site which is tough but refreshing at the same time. This place has different topographies, from dense forests to rocky slopes. It’s a treat for nature lovers who enjoy the beautiful views from the mountains. Not just a pilgrimage site, you can visit to famous Girnar Sanctuary near these hills that offer safari rides during which you can spot many wild animals. \r\n    </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End Constructions Section -->', '<!-- ======= Features Section ======= -->\r\n    <section id=\"features\" class=\"features section-bg\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <h3>SAFARI TIME\r\n        </h3>\r\n        <p>\r\n          During summer, that is from 1st March to 15th June, the timings of the safari are from 6:00 AM to 9:00 AM and 4 PM to 7 PM\r\n         \r\n        </p>\r\n        <p> During winter, that is from 16th October To 28th/29th February, the timings of safaris are from 6:45 AM to 9:45 AM and 3 PM to 6 PM\r\n        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <!-- End Features Section -->', '<!-- ======= Services Section ======= -->\r\n    <div id=\"pilgrimage\" class=\"pilgrimage\">\r\n      <div class=\"container my-4\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>Pilgrimage of Girnar\r\n          </h2>\r\n          <p>People come here for pilgrimage from various parts of the country. Girnar Hills are filled with many Hindu and Jain temples. The pilgrimage to Girnar is not just a physical journey but also a spiritual journey.\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n          <div class=\"constrain-md\">\r\n            <div class=\"card-4\">\r\n              <div class=\"\">\r\n                <h4 class=\"text-center\"> Hindu Pilgrims</h4> \r\n                  <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\r\n                    <li class=\"mb-2\">Amba Mata Temple: This is a famous Hindu Temple that is devoted to Goddess Amba. This temple is very famous among Hindus for pilgrimage. Hindus believe that if they take the blessing of Amba Mata then their all wishes will come true. </li>\r\n                    <li>Kalika Mata Temple: As its name says, this temple is devoted to Goddess Kalika. This is a famous pilgrimage site among Hindus. They believe that if they visit this temple then Mata Kalika will bless them. The surroundings of this temple are also very spiritual. \r\n                    </li> \r\n                  </ul> \r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"card-4\">\r\n              <div class=\"\">\r\n                <h4 class=\"text-center\">Jain Pilgrims</h4>   \r\n                  <ul class=\"bullet-list m-b-4\">\r\n                    <li class=\"mb-2\">Neminath Temple: This temple is a famous pilgrimage site of Jains. This one is dedicated to Lord Neminath. He was famous as the 22nd Tirthankara in Jain Dharm. Pilgrims come here to take blessings.  \r\n                    </li>\r\n                    <li>Parshwanath Temple: As the name says, this famous Jain temple is dedicated to Lord Parshwanath. He is also the 23rd Tirthankara. The people who follow Jain Dharm believe that visiting this temple will bring blessing and harmony. \r\n                    </li> \r\n                  </ul> \r\n                \r\n              </div>\r\n             \r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    <!-- End Services Section -->', '<section id=\"constructions\" class=\"\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>Religious Festivals\r\n          </h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            Girnar Hills is a must-visit destination during the festival season, especially during Navratri. It attracts pilgrims in large numbers during the festival season. This place is filled with Hindu and Jain pilgrimage temples and because of this reason, this place gets charged with devotion and happiness during festivals. \r\n          </p>\r\n        \r\n      </div>\r\n    </div></section>', '<section id=\"constructions\" class=\"\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\r\n        <div class=\"section-header\">\r\n          <h2>Historical Marvels\r\n          </h2>\r\n          <p>\r\n            Girnar hills are filled with many old Hindu and Jain temples. Not only these temples but there is a 16th-century Jama Masjid also that can be found here. This place also has several historical monuments such as the Uparkot Fort, which dates back to the Mauryan period, along with Ashoka’s rock edicts dating back to the 3rd century BCE. \r\n          </p>         \r\n      </div>\r\n    </div></section>', '<!-- ======= Features Section ======= -->\r\n    <section id=\"features\" class=\"features section-bg\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <h3>Best Time to Visit Girnar Hills </h3>\r\n        <p>\r\n          You can go to Girnar at any time of the year but the best time is from October to March, during this time many festivals are celebrated here and the climate or weather is also nice for pilgrimage purposes. You should avoid going there in summer because it can cause sunburn and heat stroke. If you want to take good pictures of scenic views then you should go from July to September because during this time the sunsets and sunrises are great but it can be a little bit challenging to trek because of the rain.\r\n        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <!-- End Features Section -->', '<p><br></p>', '2024-03-04 11:24:12', '2024-03-16 02:43:45'),
